COMMON INGREDIENTS (FOUND IN SKYRIM WILDERNESS)

Blue Mountain Flower
  VITALIS [P]
  CAECITAS [S]    (resist magic property in Skyrim maps to concealment of self)
  Use: Primary healing source. Foundational recipe ingredient.

Wheat
  VITALIS [P]
  FORTITAS [S]   (fortify health maps to physical hardening/resilience)
  Use: Most common VITALIS secondary. Combines with Blue Mountain Flower
  for the basic healing potion. Clean: no opposition interactions.

Blisterwort
  VITALIS [P]
  FORTITAS [S]
  Use: Alternative to Wheat in healing compounds. Stronger VITALIS expression.

Imp Stool
  VENITAS [P]    (damage health)
  VITALIS [S]    (restore health — secondary, creates design tension)
  GRAVITAS [T]   (ravage speed in Skyrim)
  GM NOTE: This ingredient is a perfect teaching tool for the Opposition system.
  A player combining Imp Stool with Blue Mountain Flower has VENITAS[P] vs VITALIS[P]
  — PRIMARY NEGATION. The brew collapses. A Novice who doesn't know the secondaries
  yet might not realize this is coming.

Deathbell
  VENITAS [P]    (damage health)
  GRAVITAS [S]   (slow)
  Use: Primary poison base. Common in poisoner kits.

Skeever Tail
  VENITAS [P]    (damage health)
  AGILITAS [T]   (ravage skill, loosening of control — marginal)
  Use: Basic poison source. Easy to obtain.

Mora Tapinella
  VENITAS [S]    (damage health secondary)
  ANIMA [P]      (restore magicka — spirit/mind adjacent; also hallucination properties)
  AGILITAS [T]   (regenerate stamina)
  GM NOTE: The ANIMA/VENITAS pairing here is NOT an opposition pair.
  ANIMA opposes FORTITAS, not VENITAS. These two express independently.

Thistle Branch
  GRAVITAS [P]   (resist frost maps to anchoring/hardening against cold — but note:
                  frost resist in our system is FORTITAS+GLACIES, so this is better
                  mapped as GRAVITAS since Thistle also has Slow effect)
  FORTITAS [S]   (resist frost: physical hardening against elemental)
  GM NOTE: Thistle Branch is a dual-purpose ingredient. Use your judgment on which
  property the player is targeting. If they describe wanting to slow someone, the
  GRAVITAS is primary. If they describe cold resistance, frame FORTITAS as the
  expressed Essence with GLACIES implied.

Swamp Fungal Pod
  AGILITAS [P]   (paralysis — note: paralysis is AGILITAS at extreme high concentration
                  overwhelming the nervous system, the opposite of its healing expression;
                  functionally it is AGILITAS applied adversely)
  CAECITAS [S]   (resist shock — concealment from electrical force maps here loosely)
  GM NOTE: AGILITAS at very high concentration can paradoxically produce paralysis --
  the flooding of the speed-channels overwhelms the nervous system. Treat this as a
  recognized edge case of the craft; it is also how Paralysis Poison is built (Section 9).

Canis Root
  AGILITAS [P]   (fortify one-handed, paralysis — speed and precision)
  GRAVITAS [S]   (damage stamina — weight on the system)
  GM NOTE: Canis Root has an internal AGILITAS[P]/GRAVITAS[S] tension.
  This is SECONDARY NEGATION — both Essences are present but the AGILITAS
  dominates. The GRAVITAS is significantly weakened. The compound skews speed
  but with some drag on the system.

Juniper Berries
  AGILITAS [P]   (fortify marksman — speed and precision of shot)
  VENITAS [S]    (damage stamina regen — entropy on the stamina system)
  Use: Speed-adjacent. The VENITAS[S] is not opposed to AGILITAS (GRAVITAS opposes it),
  so both express. A brewer using Juniper Berries gets speed effects with a mild
  stamina-drain secondary.

Luna Moth Wing
  CAECITAS [P]   (invisibility)
  FORTITAS [S]   (fortify one-handed — physical empowerment)
  Use: Primary invisibility source. Clean CAECITAS carrier.

Nirnroot
  CAECITAS [P]   (damage health — adverse concealment: used to dull/blind the body)
  VENITAS [S]    (damage stamina)
  FULGUR [T]     (the luminous glow and magical resonance map to FULGUR)
  GM NOTE: Nirnroot's CAECITAS[P] vs FULGUR[T] — TERTIARY NEGATION only.
  The glow barely affects the concealment property. This is the ingredient's
  famous magical paradox: it glows (FULGUR) but its dominant property is
  concealment/dulling (CAECITAS). Slight weakening on both, negligible in play.

Chaurus Eggs
  FULGUR [P]     (resist shock)
  CAECITAS [S]   (invisibility)
  FORTITAS [T]   (fortify stamina — physical hardening)
  GM NOTE: CAECITAS[S] vs FULGUR[P] — SECONDARY NEGATION on the CAECITAS.
  The invisibility property of Chaurus Eggs is significantly weakened.
  This is canon-accurate: Chaurus Eggs are primarily used for shock effects,
